{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"seedy-edema-groan","description":"# Size: split config.py + extract reconcile _run_differs + proactively split near-cap files\n\n## What\n- `config.py` (1310): extract the dataclass/schema from the env/CLI-override + cache machinery along the existing seam; collapse the `_SECTIONS` vs per-class dual source of truth where feasible.\n- `reconcile.py` (1485): extract the `_run_differs` phase (382 LOC) into a sibling `run_differs.py` along the phase seam the sequencer already carves.\n- Proactively split the 8 files within 25 LOC of the cap along their named seams (editor `_Handler`, batch_dispatch per-ticket dispatch, transition `transition_compute` — see item 12, etc.).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] config.py under cap (or materially reduced) with the schema extracted; no behavior change (config tests green).\n- [ ] `_run_differs` lives in a sibling module; reconcile.py reduced; reconciler suites green.\n- [ ] At least the top near-cap growers split along real seams (no <100-LOC fragments).\n- [ ] `make lint` + full suite green; commit(s) carry `rebar-ticket:` trailers.","id":"b043-9490-32ca-4548","parent_id":"9322-f84a-e047-4471","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Size: split config.py + extract reconcile _run_differs + proactively split near-cap files"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783056815137117001,"uuid":"a5722316-a636-4368-84b6-fa0126678dd9"}